obo:GO_0048488  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1632  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors use dynamin 1 knock out (KO) mice, dynamin 3 KO mice and dynamin 1/3 double KO mice. Using cultured cortical neurons with vGlut1-pHlourin, they demonstrate in fig 4B that fluorescence recovery after stimulation, which is indicative of synaptic vesicle (SV) endocytosis is decreased in dynamin 1 KO mice, is not effected in dynamin 3 KO mice, but is dramatically reduced in dynamin 1/3 double KO mice. Thus, dynamin 1 and 3, which together account for the overwhelming majority of brain dynamin, cooperate in supporting optimal rates of synaptic vesicle endocytosis. Experimental description: From the abstract, \"Although lack of dynamin 3 does not produce an overt phenotype in mice, it worsens the dynamin 1 KO phenotype, leading to perinatal lethality and a more severe defect in activity-dependent synaptic vesicle endocytosis\"." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1632" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

